48/*
49 * DTrace Dynamic Tracing Software: Library Interfaces
50 *
51 * Note: The contents of this file are private to the implementation of the
52 * Solaris system and DTrace subsystem and are subject to change at any time
53 * without notice. Applications and drivers using these interfaces will fail
54 * to run on future releases. These interfaces should not be used for any
55 * purpose except those expressly outlined in dtrace(7D) and libdtrace(3LIB).
56 * Please refer to the "Solaris Dynamic Tracing Guide" for more information.
57 */

94/*
95 * DTrace Program Interface
96 *
97 * DTrace programs can be created by compiling ASCII text files containing
98 * D programs or by compiling in-memory C strings that specify a D program.
99 * Once created, callers can examine the list of program statements and
100 * enable the probes and actions described by these statements.
101 */
102
103typedef struct dtrace_proginfo {
104 dtrace_attribute_t dpi_descattr; /* minimum probedesc attributes */
105 dtrace_attribute_t dpi_stmtattr; /* minimum statement attributes */
106 uint_t dpi_aggregates; /* number of aggregates specified in program */
107 uint_t dpi_recgens; /* number of record generating probes in prog */
108 uint_t dpi_matches; /* number of probes matched by program */
109 uint_t dpi_speculations; /* number of speculations specified in prog */
110} dtrace_proginfo_t;
111
112#define DTRACE_C_DIFV 0x0001 /* DIF verbose mode: show each compiled DIFO */
113#define DTRACE_C_EMPTY 0x0002 /* Permit compilation of empty D source files */
114#define DTRACE_C_ZDEFS 0x0004 /* Permit probe defs that match zero probes */
115#define DTRACE_C_EATTR 0x0008 /* Error if program attributes less than min */
116#define DTRACE_C_CPP 0x0010 /* Preprocess input file with cpp(1) utility */
117#define DTRACE_C_KNODEF 0x0020 /* Permit unresolved kernel symbols in DIFO */
118#define DTRACE_C_UNODEF 0x0040 /* Permit unresolved user symbols in DIFO */
119#define DTRACE_C_PSPEC 0x0080 /* Interpret ambiguous specifiers as probes */
120#define DTRACE_C_ETAGS 0x0100 /* Prefix error messages with error tags */
121#define DTRACE_C_ARGREF 0x0200 /* Do not require all macro args to be used */
122#define DTRACE_C_DEFARG 0x0800 /* Use 0/"" as value for unspecified args */
123#define DTRACE_C_NOLIBS 0x1000 /* Do not process D system libraries */
124#define DTRACE_C_CTL 0x2000 /* Only process control directives */
125#define DTRACE_C_MASK 0x3bff /* mask of all valid flags to dtrace_*compile */
126

219/*
220 * DTrace Formatted Output Interfaces
221 *
222 * To format output associated with a given dtrace_stmtdesc, the caller can
223 * invoke one of the following functions, passing the opaque dtsd_fmtdata and a
224 * list of record descriptions. These functions return either -1 to indicate
225 * an error, or a positive integer indicating the number of records consumed.
226 * For anonymous enablings, the consumer can use the dtrd_format member of
227 * the record description to obtain a format description. The dtfd_string
228 * member of the format description may be passed to dtrace_print{fa}_create()
229 * to create the opaque format data.
230 */
231extern void *dtrace_printf_create(dtrace_hdl_t *, const char *);
232extern void *dtrace_printa_create(dtrace_hdl_t *, const char *);
233extern size_t dtrace_printf_format(dtrace_hdl_t *, void *, char *, size_t);
234
235extern int dtrace_fprintf(dtrace_hdl_t *, FILE *, void *,
236 const dtrace_probedata_t *, const dtrace_recdesc_t *, uint_t,
237 const void *, size_t);
238
239extern int dtrace_fprinta(dtrace_hdl_t *, FILE *, void *,
240 const dtrace_probedata_t *, const dtrace_recdesc_t *, uint_t,
241 const void *, size_t);
242
243extern int dtrace_system(dtrace_hdl_t *, FILE *, void *,
244 const dtrace_probedata_t *, const dtrace_recdesc_t *, uint_t,
245 const void *, size_t);
246
247extern int dtrace_freopen(dtrace_hdl_t *, FILE *, void *,
248 const dtrace_probedata_t *, const dtrace_recdesc_t *, uint_t,
249 const void *, size_t);
250
251/*
252 * Type-specific output printing
253 *
254 * The print() action will associate a string data record that is actually the
255 * fully-qualified type name of the data traced by the DIFEXPR action. This is
256 * stored in the same 'format' record from the kernel, but we know by virtue of
257 * the fact that the action is still DIFEXPR that it is actually a reference to
258 * plain string data.
259 */
260extern int dtrace_print(dtrace_hdl_t *, FILE *, const char *,
261 caddr_t, size_t);

358#define DTRACE_A_PERCPU 0x0001
359#define DTRACE_A_KEEPDELTA 0x0002
360#define DTRACE_A_ANONYMOUS 0x0004
361#define DTRACE_A_TOTAL 0x0008
362#define DTRACE_A_MINMAXBIN 0x0010

364#define DTRACE_A_HASPOSITIVES 0x0040

366#define DTRACE_AGGZOOM_MAX 0.95 /* height of max bar */
367
368#define DTRACE_AGGWALK_ERROR -1 /* error while processing */
369#define DTRACE_AGGWALK_NEXT 0 /* proceed to next element */
370#define DTRACE_AGGWALK_ABORT 1 /* abort aggregation walk */
371#define DTRACE_AGGWALK_CLEAR 2 /* clear this element */
372#define DTRACE_AGGWALK_NORMALIZE 3 /* normalize this element */
373#define DTRACE_AGGWALK_DENORMALIZE 4 /* denormalize this element */
374#define DTRACE_AGGWALK_REMOVE 5 /* remove this element */

376struct dtrace_aggdata {
377 dtrace_hdl_t *dtada_handle; /* handle to DTrace library */
378 dtrace_aggdesc_t *dtada_desc; /* aggregation description */
379 dtrace_eprobedesc_t *dtada_edesc; /* enabled probe description */
380 dtrace_probedesc_t *dtada_pdesc; /* probe description */
381 caddr_t dtada_data; /* pointer to raw data */
382 uint64_t dtada_normal; /* the normal -- 1 for denorm */
383 size_t dtada_size; /* total size of the data */
384 caddr_t dtada_delta; /* delta data, if available */
385 caddr_t *dtada_percpu; /* per CPU data, if avail */
386 caddr_t *dtada_percpu_delta; /* per CPU delta, if avail */
387 int64_t dtada_total; /* per agg total, if avail */
388 uint16_t dtada_minbin; /* minimum bin, if avail */
389 uint16_t dtada_maxbin; /* maximum bin, if avail */
390 uint32_t dtada_flags; /* flags */
391};

453/*
454 * DTrace Object, Symbol, and Type Interfaces
455 *
456 * Library clients can use libdtrace to perform symbol and C type information
457 * lookups by symbol name, symbol address, or C type name, or to lookup meta-
458 * information cached for each of the program objects in use by DTrace. The
459 * resulting struct contain pointers to arbitrary-length strings, including
460 * object, symbol, and type names, that are persistent until the next call to
461 * dtrace_update(). Once dtrace_update() is called, any cached values must
462 * be flushed and not used subsequently by the client program.
463 */
464
465#define DTRACE_OBJ_EXEC ((const char *)0L) /* primary executable file */
466#define DTRACE_OBJ_RTLD ((const char *)1L) /* run-time link-editor */
467#define DTRACE_OBJ_CDEFS ((const char *)2L) /* C include definitions */
468#define DTRACE_OBJ_DDEFS ((const char *)3L) /* D program definitions */
469#define DTRACE_OBJ_EVERY ((const char *)-1L) /* all known objects */
470#define DTRACE_OBJ_KMODS ((const char *)-2L) /* all kernel objects */
471#define DTRACE_OBJ_UMODS ((const char *)-3L) /* all user objects */
472
473typedef struct dtrace_objinfo {
474 const char *dto_name; /* object file scope name */
475 const char *dto_file; /* object file path (if any) */
476 int dto_id; /* object file id (if any) */
477 uint_t dto_flags; /* object flags (see below) */
478 GElf_Addr dto_text_va; /* address of text section */
479 GElf_Xword dto_text_size; /* size of text section */
480 GElf_Addr dto_data_va; /* address of data section */
481 GElf_Xword dto_data_size; /* size of data section */
482 GElf_Addr dto_bss_va; /* address of BSS */
483 GElf_Xword dto_bss_size; /* size of BSS */
484} dtrace_objinfo_t;
485
486#define DTRACE_OBJ_F_KERNEL 0x1 /* object is a kernel module */
487#define DTRACE_OBJ_F_PRIMARY 0x2 /* object is a primary module */
488
489typedef int dtrace_obj_f(dtrace_hdl_t *, const dtrace_objinfo_t *, void *);
490
491extern int dtrace_object_iter(dtrace_hdl_t *, dtrace_obj_f *, void *);
492extern int dtrace_object_info(dtrace_hdl_t *, const char *, dtrace_objinfo_t *);
493

531/*

533 *
534 * Library clients can use these functions to iterate over the set of available
535 * probe definitions and inquire as to their attributes. The probe iteration
536 * interfaces report probes that are declared as well as those from dtrace(7D).
537 */
538typedef struct dtrace_probeinfo {
539 dtrace_attribute_t dtp_attr; /* name attributes */
540 dtrace_attribute_t dtp_arga; /* arg attributes */
541 const dtrace_typeinfo_t *dtp_argv; /* arg types */
542 int dtp_argc; /* arg count */
543} dtrace_probeinfo_t;
544
545typedef int dtrace_probe_f(dtrace_hdl_t *, const dtrace_probedesc_t *, void *);
546
547extern int dtrace_probe_iter(dtrace_hdl_t *,
548 const dtrace_probedesc_t *pdp, dtrace_probe_f *, void *);
549
550extern int dtrace_probe_info(dtrace_hdl_t *,
551 const dtrace_probedesc_t *, dtrace_probeinfo_t *);
552
553/*
554 * DTrace Vector Interface
555 *
556 * The DTrace library normally speaks directly to dtrace(7D). However,
557 * this communication may be vectored elsewhere. Consumers who wish to
558 * perform a vectored open must fill in the vector, and use the dtrace_vopen()
559 * entry point to obtain a library handle.
560 */
561struct dtrace_vector {
562#ifdef illumos
563 int (*dtv_ioctl)(void *, int, void *);
564#else
565 int (*dtv_ioctl)(void *, u_long, void *);
566#endif
567 int (*dtv_lookup_by_addr)(void *, GElf_Addr, GElf_Sym *,
568 dtrace_syminfo_t *);
569 int (*dtv_status)(void *, processorid_t);
570 long (*dtv_sysconf)(void *, int);
571};

573/*
574 * DTrace Utility Functions
575 *
576 * Library clients can use these functions to convert addresses strings, to
577 * convert between string and integer probe descriptions and the
578 * dtrace_probedesc_t representation, and to perform similar conversions on
579 * stability attributes.
580 */
581extern int dtrace_addr2str(dtrace_hdl_t *, uint64_t, char *, int);
582extern int dtrace_uaddr2str(dtrace_hdl_t *, pid_t, uint64_t, char *, int);
583
584extern int dtrace_xstr2desc(dtrace_hdl_t *, dtrace_probespec_t,
585 const char *, int, char *const [], dtrace_probedesc_t *);
586
587extern int dtrace_str2desc(dtrace_hdl_t *, dtrace_probespec_t,
588 const char *, dtrace_probedesc_t *);
589
590extern int dtrace_id2desc(dtrace_hdl_t *, dtrace_id_t, dtrace_probedesc_t *);
591
592#define DTRACE_DESC2STR_MAX 1024 /* min buf size for dtrace_desc2str() */
593
594extern char *dtrace_desc2str(const dtrace_probedesc_t *, char *, size_t);
595
596#define DTRACE_ATTR2STR_MAX 64 /* min buf size for dtrace_attr2str() */
597
598extern char *dtrace_attr2str(dtrace_attribute_t, char *, size_t);
599extern int dtrace_str2attr(const char *, dtrace_attribute_t *);
600
601extern const char *dtrace_stability_name(dtrace_stability_t);
602extern const char *dtrace_class_name(dtrace_class_t);
603
604extern int dtrace_provider_modules(dtrace_hdl_t *, const char **, int);
605
606extern const char *const _dtrace_version;
607extern int _dtrace_debug;
